      <hr />
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <div class="definition">
         <div>
            <p>Codes for languages associated with the entity described in the record. 
               				Includes the language a person uses when writing for publication, broadcasting, 
               				etc., a language a corporate body uses in its communications, a language of a 
               				family, or a language in which a work is expressed.
            </p>
         </div>
      </div>
      <hr />
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <div class="guidelines">
         <div>
            <p></p>
         </div>
         <h4><span class="box">â </span> INDICATORS
         </h4>
         <div class="indicators">
            <div class="indicator">
               <div>
                  <p><strong>First Indicator - Undefined</strong></p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Undefined and contains a blank (#).</p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="indicator">
               <div>
                  <p><strong>Second Indicator - Source of code</strong></p>
                  <div></div>
                  <div class="value">
                     <div><span class="valueLabel"># - MARC language code</span><div>
                           <p>Code from: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/languages/langhome.html">MARC Code List
                                    								for Languages</a></em>.
                           </p>
                        </div>
                     </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="value">
                     <div><span class="valueLabel">7 - Source specified in $2</span><div>
                           <p>Source of language code is indicated by a code in $2.</p>
                        </div>
                     </div>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
         <h4><span class="box">â </span> SUBFIELD CODES
         </h4>
         <div class="subfields">
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$a - Language code</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>A language code identifying the language that a person, organization,
                        						or family uses for publication, communication, etc., or in which a work
                        						is expressed.
                     </p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td>100</td>
                           <td colspan="9">1#$aNabokov, Vladimir,$d1899-1977</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>377</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>rus<strong>$a</strong>eng
                           </td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$l - Language term</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Language that a person, organization, or family uses for publication, 
                        						communication, etc., or in which a work is expressed.
                     </p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td>130</td>
                           <td colspan="9">#0$aBible.$lLenje.$f2003</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>377</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>bnt<strong>$l</strong>Lenje<em><span><br /><span>[The Lenje language falls under the collective code
                                       							of bnt (Bantu (Other))]</span></span></em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td>100</td>
                           <td colspan="9">1#$aZingani, Willie T.</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>377</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>eng
                           </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>377</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>nya<strong>$l</strong>Chewa<em><span><br /><span>[Zingani writes in both the Chewa dialect (which is under the 
                                       							collective code nya (Nyanja)) and in English.]</span></span></em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$2 - Source of code</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Specifies a code that identifies the source of the language code in subfield $a.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                     <p>Code from: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/standards/sourcelist/language.html">Language Code and Term Source Codes</a></em>.
                     </p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td>110</td>
                           <td colspan="9">2#$aCanadian Standards Association</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>377</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>eng<strong>$a</strong>fre
                           </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>377</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>#7</strong><strong>$a</strong>en<strong>$a</strong>fr<strong>$2</strong>iso639-1
                           </td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$6 - Linkage</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/authority/ecadcntf.html">Control Subfields</a></em>.
                     </p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$8 - Field link and sequence number</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/authority/ecadcntf.html">Control Subfields</a></em>.
                     </p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
      </div>
      <hr />
